{
  "stem": "14060.9",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And one thing I forgot to tell you, which I personally can say on the emotional side, after the war, when I got to know-- immediately after the liberation, I read myself the records-- of what happened to my father and my brother, there was one day when I was terribly upset.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And I was crying and whatnot.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And I said to myself, right, there are two ways we can get over that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Either I jump out-- it was on the third floor in the hospital-- and that's the end of it, or I will soldier on and, regardless of what happened, carry on.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And fortunately, I [LAUGHS] liked myself probably too much.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "I decided on the latter one.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But there was a crisis at all times.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "It-- I don't think there was a single person who didn't have, at a particular time, a crisis.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I would like to mention here something which is maybe a very dangerous subject-- the religion and the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Unfortunately, the religious-- very religious Hasidic Jewry of Europe-- got decimated and lost.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I mean, the Polish Jewry of three and a half million people, hardly 35,000 survived, which most of them survived in Russia and not in the camps.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "But that was a six-year period different than in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And I must say that, after the war, nobody had an answer to what has happened.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "The irreligious ones said, it all happened because you walked around in beards and payos.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "The religious ones said, it all happened because you tried to fraternize and assimilate and treat yourself like if you are a non-Jew, and they knew you were a Jew.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "So there was two opposing corners.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
